# Key Findings — 15 Minutes Bites

## Finding 1: Revenue Concentration
- 3 out of 15 menu items drove 70%+ of total revenue
- Remaining 12 items contributed less than 30% combined
- Classic 80/20 rule in action

## Finding 2: Demand Spike
- Clear 30-minute demand window before iftar every day
- Orders in this window were 3x higher than any other period
- Predictable and consistent across all days analyzed

## Finding 3: Sehri vs Iftar
- Iftar window significantly outperformed sehri
- Sehri orders were lower but more consistent throughout window

## Business Decisions Made
1. Kitchen restructured prep around top 3 platters
2. Delivery riders pre-positioned during iftar window
3. Low-performing items deprioritized from active promotion

## PM Translation
- Top 3 items = feature prioritization (focus on what drives value)
- Iftar spike = rollout timing insight (when to push notifications)
- Dashboard = self-service analytics for non-technical stakeholders
